cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the use of variational inference for optimizing a learned dynamics model in multi-agent RL. Additionally, it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with decision making in multi-agent scenarios. The paper also focuses on multi-agent RL, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Furthermore, the evaluation of the proposed method on a simulated RoboCup domain suggests that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the use of risk-sensitive optimization in the proposed method suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
